FT  17 AUG 93 / Joint venture for gas sales
SCOTTISH Hydro-Electric has formed a joint venture with a subsidiary of the
US oil company Marathon to sell gas to commercial and industrial customers.
The joint-venture company, Vector Gas, will initially sell gas in
Hydro-Electric's electricity licence area in the north of Scotland but will
later operate in England and Wales. Hydro-Electric's partner is Marathon
Gas, which sells gas from the North Sea's Brae fields, where Marathon Oil is
operator.
